      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form uncertainty quantification not required at MRL 2; turbulence model selection must be documented.",
      "rationale": "Model form uncertainty quantification is not required at MRL 2. The SST k-omega turbulence model was selected based on published literature for rotodynamic blood pump simulations. Hemolysis power-law model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) is standard for this application."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Input parameter sensitivity must be documented at MRL 2; formal uncertainty propagation not required.",
      "rationale": "Model input sensitivity to hematocrit (40 +/- 2%), blood viscosity, and inlet velocity profile was evaluated via one-at-a-time sensitivity analysis. NIH showed less than 4% sensitivity to input variations within specified ranges. Formal UQ not required at MRL 2."
    },
